 legal help, being a leading and unifying voice, and establishing a center for innovation, training, and expertise','https://www.tals.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(65,'Legal Aid Services of Oklahoma','Legal Aid Services of Oklahoma helps provide residents of Oklahoma with access to legal information and services, including forms, court help, and finding representation.','https://oklaw.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(66,'Kansas Legal Services','Kansas Legal Services, a statewide non-profit corporation, is devoted to helping low income Kansans meet their basic needs through the provision of important legal and mediation services.','https://www.kansaslegalservices.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(67,'Colorado Legal Services','Colorado Legal Services (CLS) is a non-profit providing, if eligible, free legal advice, clinics and representation to low-income Coloradans and seniors.','https://www.coloradolegalservices.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(68,'Utah Legal Services','This website provides legal information to citizens of Utah.','https://www.utahlegalservices.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(69,'Nevada Legal Services','Nevada Legal Services can help with a variety of legal issues. They primarily assist with housing cases where tenants are facing eviction or termination of their subsidized housing, where individuals and families are applying for and are denied or terminated from SNAP, TANF, or other government benefits, denials of Unemployment Benefits and Pandemic Unemployment Assistance, sealing criminal and eviction records, and more. ','https://nevadalegalservices.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(70,'Pine Tree Legal Assistance (Maine)','Pine Tree Legal Assistance is committed to making the justice system more accessible for all Mainers, regardless of income. Some of the aspects of the legal process they help with include advocacy, providing quality information about your rights, and providing community legal education.','http://ptla.org/our-mission-and-services','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(71,'New Hampshire Legal Aid','This website\'s purpose is to assist in the delivery of legal services to low-income clients and to provide accurate information to the community. It is a joint effort of the Legal Services Agencies serving New Hampshire\'s low-income population.','https://nhlegalaid.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(72,'Vermont Legal Aid','Vermont Legal Aid is a website that contains information pertaining to Vermont residents about legal issues.','https://www.vtlawhelp.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(73,'Mass Legal Help (Massachusetts)','Mass Legal Healp connects, supports, and educates advocates and the general public on legal information. The content on our website is written by people in the legal services community.','https://www.masslegalhelp.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(74,'CT Law Help','CTLawHelp.org was created by several nonprofit legal services organizations whose shared mission is to improve the lives of Connecticut\'s poorest citizens by providing free legal services to people with low income. This website, funded by the Connecticut Bar Foundation and the Legal Services Corporation, seeks to further the goal of equal access to justice by providing information and self-help materials on legal issues affecting people with low income.','https://ctlawhelp.org/en/home','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(75,'Legal Services of New Jersey','Legal Services of New Jersey (LSNJ) is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit offering free legal advice to low-income people in New Jersey. Find legal information by clicking on a legal topic or typing a few words into the search box.','https://www.lsnjlaw.org/Pages/index.aspx','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(76,'Law Help NY','LawHelpNY.org, powered by Pro Bono Net, is an online tool for helping low-income New Yorkers solve their legal problems.','https://www.lawhelpny.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(77,'PA Law Help','PALawHELP.org is a guide to legal information and free civil legal services for low-income persons and seniors in Pennsylvania. Here you can locate information on a variety of legal issues, as well as information on how to contact programs providing legal assistance in Pennsylvania.','https://www.palawhelp.org/about-us','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(78,'Ohio Legal Help','Ohio Legal Help leverages technology and innovation to improve justice and fairness for all Ohioans. This website tries to make sure all Ohioans can understand their legal options, make informed decisions and connect to legal and community resources.','https://www.ohiolegalhelp.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(79,'Indiana Legal Services','Indiana Legal Services, Inc. (ILS) is a nonprofit law firm that provides free civil legal assistance to eligible low-income residents throughout the state of Indiana.','https://www.indianalegalservices.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(80,'Illinois Legal Aid Online','Illinois Legal Aid Online is a website that provides legal aid, information, and support to residents of Illinois.','https://www.illinoislegalaid.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(81,'Iowa Legal Aid','Iowa Legal Aid provides free civil legal assistance and does not charge our clients for legal services.','https://www.iowalegalaid.org/#','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(82,'Legal Aid of Nebraska','Legal Aid of Nebraska is a website that provides legal aid, including civil legal services, to residents of Nebraska.','https://www.legalaidofnebraska.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(83,'Iowa Legal Aid Services','Idaho Legal Aid Services, Inc. is a nonprofit statewide organization dedicated to providing equal access to justice for low-income people through quality advocacy and education.','https://www.idaholegalaid.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(84,'Legal Action of Wisconsin','Legal Action of Wisconsin is an organization providing free civil legal services to Wisconsin clients at the most vulnerable times in their lives.','https://www.legalaction.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(85,'Law Help MN','Legal Services State Support (State Support) is a project of the Minnesota Legal Services Coalition (MLSC), a group of seven legal aid programs that help low-income residents with a variety of legal matters.','https://www.lawhelpmn.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(86,'Legal Services of North Dakota','LSND\'s mission is to provide high quality legal advice, education and representation to low-income North Dakotans as well as disadvantaged elderly in areas of civil law.','http://www.legalassist.org/','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(87,'South Dakota Law Help','South Dakota Law Help is a website that provides legal information for residents of South Dakota, as well as providing legal forms and resources for no or low-cost legal representation.','https://ujslawhelp.sd.gov/default.aspx','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(88,'Alliance of Families for Justice','The Alliance of Families for Justice helps to provide a vital set of services to incarcerated individuals and their families, including legal aid, information, and representation.','https://afj-ny.org/legal-support-unit','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(89,'Legal Aid Society of New York City','The Legal Aid Society of New York City helps to protect and defend the rights of everyday New Yorkers who need legal support, regardless of who they are, where they come from, or how they identify.','https://legalaidnyc.org','Legal','State Specific Resources',1),(90,'CASA - Court Appoint Special Advocates for Children','Maryland CASA Association is a private, non-profit, 501(c)(3) organization incorporated in 1997 to facilitate the continued development and success of Maryland\'s Court Appointed Special Advocate (CASA) programs to ensure that every abused and